## Step 1 — Scan the Target Page DOM

After reading the project context, call the MCP tool to scan the page:

**Tool:** `scan_page_selectors(url, headless=true, min_score=20)`

From the scan result extract:
- `selectors[]` — ranked list of elements with `constant_name`, `selector`, `strategy`, `score`, `tag`, `text`
- `java_constants` — pre-formatted Java constant block

**Selector Priority (always respect this order):**
| Score | Strategy | Example |
|-------|----------|---------|
| 100 | testId | `[data-testid='login-btn']` |
| 90 | aria-label | `[aria-label='Username']` |
| 85 | id (non-dynamic) | `#username` |
| 80 | name | `input[name='email']` |
| 75 | placeholder | `input[placeholder='Search']` |
| 70 | type | `input[type='password']` |
| 50 | stable class | `button.submit-btn` |
| 20 | xpath-text | `//button[normalize-space()='Login']` |

Flag selectors with score < 30 with: `// ⚠ low-confidence — verify manually`

If page scan fails (auth wall, timeout): tell the user, ask if they can share the HTML or a screenshot instead.

