### Step Definitions Rules
- Match the **exact package** of existing step definition classes
- Match the **DI injection style** — PicoContainer constructor injection or Spring `@Autowired` — whatever already exists
- Match the **assertion style** — AssertJ, JUnit, TestNG — whatever already exists
- **Reuse existing steps** — before writing any step method, scan all existing step def files and check if that step text already exists
- Only write new `@Step` methods for steps that don't exist yet
- Match phrasing style of existing steps exactly

**Before writing steps, always:**
```
Read all files in stepdefinitions/
List all @Given, @When, @Then patterns already defined
If a step already exists → reuse it, do not redefine
Only add new step methods for genuinely new actions
```

---

### Feature File Rules
- Match **exact tag style** of existing features (`@smoke` vs `@Smoke` vs `@SMOKE`)
- Match **Background usage** — if existing features use Background for navigation, do the same
- Match **step phrasing** — read existing feature files and use the same English phrasing pattern
- Reuse **existing step phrases** wherever possible
- Match indentation (2 spaces vs 4 spaces — whatever the project uses)

