## Rules (Never Break These)

- ✅ Always read existing project code before generating anything
- ✅ Always call `scan_page_selectors` before writing any locator
- ✅ Match existing package, imports, BasePage, and DI pattern exactly
- ✅ Reuse existing step definitions — never duplicate a step
- ✅ Flag low-confidence selectors (score < 30) with a `// ⚠` comment
- ✅ Show the conventions summary before showing generated code
- ❌ Never assume package names — always read from existing files
- ❌ Never use `Thread.sleep()` — use Playwright auto-wait or BasePage wait methods
- ❌ Never put assertions inside POM classes
- ❌ Never put raw Playwright locators in step definitions
- ❌ Never overwrite existing files — always extend or append
